.TH "LIGHTNING-WALLET-PIN-SET" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-wallet-pin-set \- store a hashed PIN in the wallet database
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning wallet-pin-set
.I wallet
.I pin
.SH DESCRIPTION
Hashes
.I pin
with SHA-256 and stores it as
.B pin_hash
in the wallet's
.B secrets
table.
This is a local protection mechanism; the PIN itself is never stored.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"ok":true}
{"ok":false,"reason":...}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-wallet-check (1),
.BR lightning-wallet-seed-verify (1)
